results.name: Expansion of phi(x) * chi(-x) * psi(x^3) in powers of x where phi(), psi(), chi() are Ramanujan theta functions
comment: Ramanujan theta functions: f(q) (see A121373), phi(q) (A000122), psi(q) (A010054), chi(q) (A000700).
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
Michael Somos, Introduction to Ramanujan theta functions
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Ramanujan Theta Functions
formula: Expansion of q^(-1/3) * eta(q^2)^4 * eta(q^6)^2 / (eta(q) * eta(q^3) * eta(q^4)^2) in powers of q.
program: (PARI) {a(n) = local(A); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x^2 + A)^4 * eta(x^6 + A)^2 / (eta(x + A) * eta(x^3 + A) * eta(x^4 + A)^2), n))};
